    value: 伸
english:
  title: Two Poems Sent to Shin
  author: Cao Wei
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The traveling geese cannot form their line,
    Border sounds rise as day fades away.
    Thinking of you, my hair has turned white for nothing,
    Gazing forlorn—you are a thousand miles distant.

    The mountain passes stretch long and far,
    Silently I count the steps homeward.
    When will we lie down together at night,
    Listening as one to the rain on the plum hall?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: '''Plum hall'' likely refers to a specific location of significance to the recipient, possibly a residence or meeting place where the two once shared moments together.'
